//! Qualified-construction layout fixture (owner module). Exports a monomorphic
//! record `Point` and a generic record `Holder<T>` plus a payload record `Box`.
//!
//! Under qualified-by-default the importer constructs these through their
//! module-qualified outer name (`qualshapes.Point`, `qualshapes.Holder<Box>`).
//! Every record-layout registration keys on the BARE outer name (`Point`,
//! `Holder$$Box`); the MIR `StructInit` producer, the MIR codegen-readiness
//! check, and the codegen `record_layouts` consumer must therefore shorten the
//! qualified outer name to its bare form before the field-order / layout lookup,
//! or the qualified spelling misses the registered key and the construction
//! falls through the fail-closed gate.

/// Monomorphic record reached through `qualshapes.Point`.
pub type Point {
    x: i64;
    y: i64;
}

/// Payload record for the generic instantiation.
pub type Box {
    payload: i64;
}

/// Generic record reached through `qualshapes.Holder<qualshapes.Box>`.
pub type Holder<T> {
    inner: T;
    tag: i64;
}
